                <h4>One Year (Two Semesters) of Foreign Language</h4>
                <p>Proficiency equivalent to one year of college instruction in a foreign language taught by the Department of Modern Languages and Literatures or Judaic Studies is required.  Standardized examinations for foreign languages may be used to meet the requirement.</p>

                <h4>Additional Electives</h4>
                <p>Students must fulfill both University requirements and those for their major in order to receive a bachelor's degree from UCF.  All students must earn a minimum of 120 unduplicated credit hours with at least a "C" average (2.0 GPA) for all UCF course work attempted.</p>

                <h4>Upper-Level Requirements</h4>
                <p>Must complete at least 48 of these 120 credit hours in 3000-4000 level courses (upper-division) in order to complete the degree.</p>
